verseas accounts</h3>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re paying from an overseas account use the details as below.</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Account name</th>\n      <th><abbr title=\"International Bank Account Number\">IBAN</abbr></th>\n      <th><abbr title=\"SWIFT Bank Identifier Code\">BIC</abbr></th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> Cumbernauld</td>\n      <td>GB74CITI08321012001039</td>\n      <td>CITIGB2L</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> Shipley</td>\n      <td>GB05CITI08321012001020</td>\n      <td>CITIGB2L</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>If asked for the <abbr title=\"International Bank Account Number\">IBAN</abbr>, you must also give the <abbr title=\"SWIFT Bank Identifier Code\">BIC</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>&rsquo;s banking address is Citi, Citigroup Centre, Canada Square, Canary Wharf, London E14 5LB.</p>\n\n<h3>Multiple CHAPS payments</h3>\n\n<p>To make a single payment for multiple Corporation Tax references, <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://search2.hmrc.gov.uk/kbroker/hmrc/locator/locator.jsp?type=0\" title=\"tax office locator\">contact the <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> Accounts Office</a> you normally deal with for advice.</p>\n\n<h2>Direct Debit</h2>\n\n<p>Set up a Direct Debit through your company&rsquo;s <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://online.hmrc.gov.uk/corporation-tax/\" title=\"Corporation Tax online\"><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> online account.</a> Allow 5 working days to process a Direct Debit the first time you set one up. After that, it’s 3 working days. Payments will appear on your bank statements as &ldquo;<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> NDDS&rdquo;.</p>\n\n<p>You can make changes to the Direct Debit through your company&rsquo;s <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMR