e a second notice is published in the gazzette - this means it won&rsquo;t legally exist.</p>\n\n<h2>Withdrawing your application</h2>\n\n<p>If your company stops being eligible to be struck off you must withdraw the application. To do this, send form DS02 to Companies House. Only 1 director needs to sign it. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/forms/generalForms/DS02_withdrawal_of_striking_off_application_by_company.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form DS02' (PDF, 685KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form DS02’ (PDF, 685KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You can also use this form to withdraw the application if you change your mind about striking off your company.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>More information</h2>\n\n<p>Companies House has more information about the process.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/about/pdf/gp4.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Guidance on strike off' (PDF, 115KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Guidance on strike off’ (PDF, 115KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-11-06T15:44:34+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Selling your business and closing down","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business%2Fselling-closing.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Stopping self-employment, winding up or liquidating a Ltd company and more","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=business%2Fselling-closing","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/business/selling-closing"},"parent":{"title":"Businesses and self-employed","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/business.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Information about starting up and running a business in the UK, including help if you're self employed or a sole trader.","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=business","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk